title: Race Like A Girl
description: Race Like A Girl is a "laid back" circuit race on about a 1/2 mile loop in Union Park in Des Moines. The race is designed for new racers, but experienced racers will also have fun. Race includes Women's A/B, Mens A/B, Juniors, and a kiddy race. Races are track-style formats, ie. 10 laps, points every other lap.
course: 1/2 mile paved loop, mostly flat. One small rise about 2/3 through the course. Shade and lawn to sit and watch the race. Very family friendly venue.
registration: Register day of race. USA Cycling annual license or 1-day license required. Kiddies need to also register. All USCF rules apply, helmets required, included for kids in the kiddy race. Big wheels, trikes, training wheels are fine for the kiddy race. Older kids may choose to race in the junior race.
notes: Registration opens at 4:30 p.m., Races start at 5:30 p.m., and generally will finish as darkness nears. Each racer will have a chance to race at least 3 times during the evening. No prize money, just schwag (prizes). Kiddies get cookies and medals. Kids ride is permiited under permit number 2013-1239
directions: Union Park is located in Des Moines, just north of Lutheran Hospital and just south of Birldland Marina. We race on the south loop. The street is Saylor Road. Easiest to GoogleMap Union Park Des Moines https://www.google.com/search?q=union+park+des+moines&sourceid=ie7&rls=com.microsoft:en-US:IE-Address&ie=&oe=&rlz=

title: Race Like A Girl Kid's Races
description: Kiddy Race held in conjunction with Race Like a Girl. Kids can ride big wheels, trikes, bikes with training wheels, push bikes, or uprights. This race is for kids who are too young for the competitive junior race.
course: Little kids will do a straight "sprint,", about 100 yards. Older little kids will do 1 lap, accompanied by one or more adults.
registration: FREE..but kids need to complete the waiver, wear a helmet, and pin on a race number.
notes: All the kids receive a medal and cookie. There are no official placings in this race.
directions: Union Park, Des Moines Iowa. South loop.

title: University of Iowa Hootenanny Race Weekend
Chris Lillig Memorial Cup/Old Capitol Criterium
35th Annual Melon City Criterium/ Rider Developmen
Bicycle Blues and BBQ Omnium - Midwest Flyover #4
description:
Bicycle, Blues and BBQ Festival 
July 12, 13 & 14, 2013
Clear Lake, IA
$15,000 cash prizes & primes 
Over $3,500 in merchandise prizes 

Pre-Registration is required of Omnium and ITT.  

Please join us Friday night in City Park for Blues performers Mooseknuckle Brothers and Sena Ehrhardt Band.  The first band starts at 5:30 p.m. All pre-registered riders (ages 21 and over) will receive two complimentary beer tickets to the Budweiser & Goose Island hospitality tent Friday night.  

The Bicycle, Blues and BBQ Festival is thrilled to be an omnium format and a part of the Midwest Flyover.  The goal of the omnium is to determine and reward the best all around racers in each of their respective categories.  Racers must compete in all three events to be eligible for the omnium.  Omnium results are based on points, not time.  The BBBQ Race Weekend is also race #4 of the Midwest Flyover Omnium Race Series (www.midwestflyover.com/).   

Only standard road bikes will be allowed for those competing in the Omnium.  Nearly 100% of the racers travel over 90 miles to compete. We wanted to minimize the amount of extra equipment needed to race during this weekend and to maximize the number of teammates who could travel together.   

The racing action kicks off on Saturday, July 13th with the time trial in the morning followed by a fast-paced and technical criterium, a favorite for racers and spectators alike. The criterium will crown the Iowa State Criterium Champion in each respective event.

Racing continues on Sunday, July 14th, with the road race. Starting from Tourist Park in Clear Lake, road races of 85- and 47-miles are on tap, taking in the greater North Iowa countryside.
course:
ITT:  7 mile course - out and back.
Criterium:  .77 miles course with technical turns.
Road Race:  45/83 mile course with rolling hills and a 1/2 closed road sprint to the finish.
registration:
On-line registration required for the Omnium/ITT is through USA Cycling:  On-Line registration closes at 10:00 p.m., Wednesday, July 10.  

By registering on-line for the Omnium event on USA Cycling you will automatically be entered into the TT, Criterium and Road Race events.
notes:
All festival information, race bible, maps and hotel information can be found on-line at: 
http://www.bicyclebluesbbq.com/omnium-race-weekend/
directions: On site registration and start/finish line located at City Park: N 3rd St & First Ave N, Clear Lake, IA 50428.

title: IMBCS #10 The Mullet Fall Classic
description:
On Saturday, October 5th, 2013 the Iowa Mountain Bike Championship Series heads south to Lake Ahquabi State Park for the fifth running of the event at the park. The new category of race added 2 years ago - the Marathon - will be back. Marathon Junkies will race in our very own Iowa version of riding in circles until the clock stops featuring a solo Marathon Open Class as they grind it out for as many miles as they can do before the clock says stop.

New for 2013: 

--USA Cycling Designated Iowa State Championship for XC Categories!!!!

--Fat Bike Division (non-USA Cycling category, but for The Mullet).  Fat Bikes will do 2 laps with the $25 entry fee and you will be racing the big meats for prizes.  No wimpy 3.0 tires allowed.  You have to be at least 3.7" FAT!!!

--Kids Race (kids 10 and under).  A short loop, non-competitive fun event that features treats for all after crossing the line.  Kids Race will be at 3:30 p.m.  No entry fee to register, but parents must sign the waiver.



The Mullet Fall Classic Mountain Bike Race will feature the 4 Hour Marathon (the marathon race starts at 11:00 a.m. and any lap begun before the clock hits 3:00 p.m. can be completed and counts!!!), and of course, the usual 2013 IMBCS XC race categories of Expert (4 laps), Comp (3 laps), Sport (2 laps), and Beginner (1 lap) to battle for the Mullet Classic Fall podium spots in their respective XC race categories.

This is Iowa's very own backwoods, super fast, fat tire XC race held on a course loop that rolls on the multi-use cross country ski, snowmobile, and hiking trail that circles Lake Ahquabi. This year features a 6.7 mile race loop that utilizes backwood sections of the wooded trails throughout Lake Ahquabi State Park to make for a scenic race filled with unique challenges.
course:
The 6.7 mile loop includes a trip around Lake Ahquabi's multi-use trail with additional sections that include backwood trails. You will encounter gravel, dirt, roots, ruts, grass, logs, wooden bridges, climbs, fast descents and the best nature has to offer on this scenic course. The loop will be the perfect test of one's fitness with all of the full throttle speed and all of the climbing, but will not be technical in nature to scare off the entry level racer. In fact, this will be a perfect venue for first timers and experts alike. Come and join the fun!

Start/Finish area in front of the Beach Shelter. Loop will be run in a clockwise direction.  Kids Race will be held near the beach area and be a short loop.
registration:
Registration is available online at USA Cycling and closes on Thursday, October 3rd at 10 p.m. .  

We strongly urge everyone to register online at USA Cycling as it helps us in preparing the bike numbers with the respective category tags for such a large group of racers - which is very time consuming. Entry fees are discounted for using online registration (see entry fees below).

Day of Race Registration begins at 9:30am and closes 30 minutes before your respective race for those that do not, for some reason, register online. Again, we urge you to register online to help streamline the data entry that must be done this year. Thanks!

Entry Fee: *$15-40 range

Marathon - $30 Pre-Registration/$40 Day of Race Registration

Expert Cat I - $30 Pre-Registration/$40 Day of Race Registration

Comp Cat II - $25 Pre-Registration/$35 Day of Race Registration

Sport Cat II - $25 Pre-Registration/$35 Day of Race Registration

FAT BIKES - $25 Pre-Registration/$35 Day of Race

Juniors 18 & Under - $15 Pre-Registration/$25 Day of Race Registration

Beginner Cat III - $20 Pre-Registration/$30 Day of Race Registration

Kids Race (ages 10 and under) - No Registration Fee, but parents must sign the waiver.


All proceeds from The Mullet (after expenses) will go to trail maintenance equipment for Banner Pits and Lake Ahquabi.
notes:
RACE DAY SCHEDULE:  11:00 a.m. start for the Marathon racers; 1 p.m. for all IMBCS XC category racers, with categories starting in waves as listed); 3:30 p.m. for the Kids Race


CAT 1 Expert Men/ - 1:00 pm (prizes: medals and cash payout prizes for overall top 3 in Expert Men) - 4 laps

CAT 1 Women's Open/CAT 2 Comp Men's Class - 1:02 pm (medals and cash pay out prizes for overall top 3 in Expert Women's; medals for winners in Comp) 3 laps

CAT 2 Sport Men/Sport Women - 1:04 pm (medals for winners) 2 laps

FAT BIKES - 1:04 pm (prizes for winners) 2 laps

CAT 3 Beginner Men/Beginner Women/Junior - 1:06 pm (medals for winners) 1 lap

Open Marathon Category Men Solo/Women Solo/Tandem Bike (prizes: cash pay out for top 3 in Marathon Men's Solo and Women's Solo categories; medals for tandem top 3) - 11:00 as many laps as you can fit into the time allotment!! When the clock hits 3:00 p.m., no more new laps may begin. However, if your final lap started before the clock hit 3:00 p.m. - it counts and winners will be those with the most laps done. That means the winning times for the cash will be closer to 4:00+ hours.

Kids Race (age 10 and under) - 3:30 p.m. will be a non-competitive, fun short loop less than 2km with treats for all.
directions: Lake Ahquabi State Park is five miles south of Indianola (17 miles south of Des Moines) on Hwy. 65/69 and one mile west on G-58. Enter Lake Ahquabi State Park through the main entrance where G-58 ends and the entrance gate is located at the 4 way stop. Parking and registration will be at the Lake Ahquabi Beach Shelter (once you enter the park, follow the road all the way down the hill to the beach area). We will use the Beach Shelter for the day of the race and restrooms (Porta Potties) will be located there as well.
